<p>
  According to GD 18, the following aspects are required in the reporting on the
  exceptions:
</p>
<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>Schema field</th>
      <th>Description</th>
      <th>Property</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <p>ExceptionCode</p>
      </td>
      <td>
        <p>Unique identifier code for the exception.</p>
      </td>
      <td>
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <p>ExceptionOldCode</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Exception code(s) used in 2015 Art. 14 report, if changed in 2021.
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required, where applicable</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>ExceptionName</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Short name for the exception.</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>ExceptionType</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          The most relevant MSFD Article 14 subparagraph which is applicable to
          the exception
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>ExceptionReason</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Indicates the main reason(s) for needing an exception</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Conditional: (in field &lsquo;ExceptionType&rsquo;, for all types
          except Art.14(1)(e) &ndash; Natural conditions)
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>GESachieved</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Estimated date by when GES is expected to be achieved, for an Article
          14(1)(e) exception.
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Conditional (if field &lsquo;ExceptionType&rsquo; = Art.14(1)(e)
          &ndash; Natural conditions)
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>RelevantPressures</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Pressures that are the key reason for applying the exception and which
          are preventing the achievement of GES or associated targets
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Conditional (in field &lsquo;ExceptionType&rsquo;, for all types
          except Art. 14(1)(e) and 14(4).
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>RelevantTargets</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Target(s), as reported under Art. 10, which are affected by the
          exception.
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Conditional (in field &lsquo;ExceptionType&rsquo;, for all types
          except Art. 14(4)
        </p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>GEScomponent</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>GES Descriptors and criteria affected by the exception</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle (at descriptor level only)</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>RelevantFeatures</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>List of the features affected by the exception.</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>
          Prefilled from first cycle (at broad ecosystem component level only)
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>RegionSubregion</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>MSFD region(s) and subregion(s) where the measure applies</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>Spatial scope_geographic zones</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Indicate the coverage of the exception according to the jurisdictional
          zones of MSFD marine waters.
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>MarineReportingUnit</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Area(s) affected by the exception</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>JustificationDescription</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          A specific and substantiated justification for applying the exception,
          including the evidence used, the relevant aspects of the marine
          environment affected (descriptors, features) and the areas affected
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>MeasuresAdHoc</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          List of the ad-hoc measures taken which are relevant for this
          exception
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Conditional (if exception is notified under Art. 14(1) (b), (c) or
          (d))
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>Mitigation</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Indicates the types of mitigation measures taken.</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Conditional (if exception is notified under Art. 14(1) (b), (c) or
          (d))
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td >
        <p>FurtherInformation</p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>
          Provide the section(s) of the Summary report and, if relevant, a URL
          web link to a more detailed assessment of the Art. 14 exception.
        </p>
      </td>
      <td >
        <p>Required</p>
        <p>Prefilled from first cycle</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p><br /></p>
<p><br /></p>
<p>
  The assessor should indicate whether the following aspects are specified for
  each exception:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      the relevant descriptors and targets (GEScomponent, RelevantFeatures,
      RelevantTargets)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      spatial coverage (RegionSubregion, MarineReportingUnit, Spatial
      scope_geographic zones)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">the type of exception (ExceptionType)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      in case of Art. 14(1)(e) MSFD, an estimation, of when achieving GES can be
      expected (GESachieved)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      in case of Art. 14(1)(b)-(d) planned ad hoc measures to continue pursuing
      the environmental targets, prevent further deterioration in the status of
      the marine environment and mitigate adverse impacts at the level of marine
      (sub)regions or in marine waters of other Member States. (MeasuresAdHoc,
      Mitigation).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      reasons invoked in accordance with first sub-paragraph of Article 14(1) -
      for each instance; (ExceptionReason)
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">justification / per instance (JustificationDescription).</p>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  Select &lsquo;yes&rsquo; if all the aspects are specified,
  &lsquo;partially&rsquo; if at least 1/3 of them are specified, &lsquo;not
  clear&rsquo; if the information reported is not clear and inconsistent,
  &lsquo;no&rsquo; if no or less than 1/3 of the aspects are specified. Select
  &lsquo;not relevant&rsquo; if there are no exceptions (&lsquo;no&rsquo; under
  previous question).
</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p>
  For this question, priority will be given to e-reporting as there are specific
  schema fields for each measure. If there is no information in the e-reporting,
  check the text report. Specify where this information is found in the text
  report.
</p>
